parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate excessively when braking, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates when braking
especially at high speeds or when driving downhill. The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may take longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
or it may travel all the way to the floor without engaging the brakes. The vehicle may not stop as quickly as usual
or it may not stop at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to vibrate or pulse when braking. The vehicle may also experience a loss of traction or stability when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Misfire and Piston Ring Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine misfire and piston ring failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or vibrate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk when accelerating, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
Brake problems can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, which can lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: VSA (Vehicle Stability Assist) and Check Engine Light Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: VSA and check engine light issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Illuminated VSA and check engine lights

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Other issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction or become unsafe to operate.
